# Requirements — `<feature-name>`

> EARS-style requirements. Copy this file to `specs/<feature-name>/requirements.md`
> and replace every `<placeholder>`. Every requirement must be testable.

## Context

> 1-3 sentences: why this feature exists, what problem it solves, and the
> shape of the change at 10,000 ft. Cite the row in `feature_list.json`
> (id + acceptance) the requirements derive from.

## R1 — `<short-name>`

WHEN `<event / trigger>` THE SYSTEM SHALL `<observable outcome>`.

**Acceptance signal:** `<how a test detects this is true>`

## R2 — `<short-name>`

WHILE `<state>` IS TRUE THE SYSTEM SHALL `<continuous behaviour>`.

## R3 — `<short-name>`

WHERE `<configuration / capability is present>` THE SYSTEM SHALL `<conditional behaviour>`.

## R4 — `<short-name>` (unwanted)

IF `<failure / illegal input>` THEN THE SYSTEM SHALL `<error response>`.

> **EARS legend:**
> - `WHEN ... SHALL ...` — event-driven
> - `WHILE ... SHALL ...` — state-driven
> - `WHERE ... SHALL ...` — optional/feature-gated
> - `IF ... THEN ... SHALL ...` — unwanted behaviour / failure modes
> - Plain `THE SYSTEM SHALL ...` — ubiquitous invariants

